Note:
LLVM IR Emitter - Buffered output for LLVM IR code generation

All buffer management, character/string emission, and indentation logic
is delegated to the shared byte-buffer foundation in emitter_common.runa.

Conventions:
- 2-space indentation for LLVM IR basic blocks and instructions
- Null-terminated output strings
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/emitter_common.runa" as EmitterCommon

@Reasoning:
LLVM IR is whitespace-significant only for newlines, but human readability
matters during compiler debugging. The typed wrapper distinguishes LLVM
text-IR output from other backends in the dispatch table.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Three fields shadow the raw EmitterCommon byte buffer (pointer, capacity,
length). All actual storage lives in the shared arena.
@End Implementation

Type called "LlvmIrEmitter":
    buffer as Integer
    capacity as Integer
    length as Integer
End Type

@Reasoning:
Factory entry that keeps EmitterCommon as a private dependency of this
file so hir_to_llvmir.runa never imports it directly.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_create which allocates the initial byte buffer
with EmitterCommon's default capacity.
@End Implementation

Process called "create_llvmir_emitter" returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_create from EmitterCommon
End Process

@Reasoning:
Symmetric lifecycle pair for create_llvmir_emitter.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_destroy which frees the byte buffer then the
emitter struct itself.
@End Implementation

@Security_Scope:
Caller must guarantee the handle was produced by create_llvmir_emitter
and has not already been destroyed.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "destroy_llvmir_emitter" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_destroy from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process

@Reasoning:
Lets call sites that know they are about to emit a large module
pre-grow the buffer and avoid repeated realloc churn during instruction
stream emission.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Delegates to emitter_raw_ensure_capacity which grows the buffer to at
least the requested byte count using EmitterCommon's doubling policy.
@End Implementation

Process called "ensure_capacity" takes emitter as Integer, needed as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_ensure_capacity from EmitterCommon with emitter, needed
End Process

@Reasoning:
Single-byte emission is the hot primitive for LLVM punctuation like
commas, parentheses, %, and @; exposing it directly avoids one-character
string allocations.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards the byte value to emitter_raw_emit_byte.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
Hot path. O(1) amortized.
@End Performance_Hints

Process called "emit_char" takes emitter as Integer, char as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, char
End Process

@Reasoning:
Bulk emission for LLVM opcodes, types, and identifiers.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_emit_string which walks the null-terminated input
and copies bytes into the buffer.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
Hot path. O(n) in input length.
@End Performance_Hints

Process called "emit_string" takes emitter as Integer, str as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, str
End Process

@Reasoning:
LLVM IR is statement-per-line, so emit_line is one of the most-called
helpers in the backend.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits the string then appends ASCII LF (10). LLVM tooling accepts LF on
all supported platforms.
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_line" takes emitter as Integer, str as Integer returns Integer:
    proc emitter_raw_emit_string from EmitterCommon with emitter, str
    proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Standalone newline used when terminating a basic block label or inserting
a blank separator between functions; not coupled to a preceding string.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits ASCII LF (10) as a single byte.
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_newline" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 10
End Process

@Reasoning:
Spaces are emitted between every LLVM opcode and operand pair; isolating
the literal 32 keeps the backend free of magic numbers.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits ASCII SPACE (32).
@End Implementation

Process called "emit_space" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 32
End Process

@Reasoning:
LLVM IR canonical formatting uses 2-space indentation for instructions
inside basic blocks; matching this avoids spurious diffs against
llvm-as round-trips.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Multiplies the indent level by 2 to obtain the space count, then emits
that many ASCII SPACE bytes.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(level) bytes. Called once per emitted instruction.
@End Performance_Hints

Process called "emit_indent" takes emitter as Integer, level as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: 2-space indentation for LLVM IR basic blocks and instructions.
    Let total_spaces be level multiplied by 2
    Let count be 0
    While count is less than total_spaces:
        proc emitter_raw_emit_byte from EmitterCommon with emitter, 32
        Set count to count plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the accumulated LLVM IR text so the driver can hand it to disk
or to llvm-as without copying.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_get_output which terminates the buffer and
returns its base pointer.
@End Implementation

@Security_Scope:
Returned pointer aliases the emitter's internal buffer. Caller must not
free it directly and must not use it after destroy_llvmir_emitter.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "get_output" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_get_output from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process

@Reasoning:
Exposes the current byte count so tests and golden-output diff tools can
detect empty or unexpectedly short generation results.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_length.
@End Implementation

Process called "get_length" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_length from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process

@Reasoning:
Lets the driver reuse a single emitter across multiple translation units
without paying allocation cost for each one.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Forwards to emitter_raw_reset which zeroes the length field but keeps
the buffer allocation intact.
@End Implementation

Process called "reset" takes emitter as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc emitter_raw_reset from EmitterCommon with emitter
End Process
